Name: Yousef El-Kurdi

Suggested reference: http://vimcasts.org/episodes/synchronizing-plugins-with-git-submodules-and-pathogen/

Installation:
  1-  Clone the configurations:
    $> git clone https://github.com/yelkurdi/dotvim.git ~/.vim

  *-  Execute install.sh, or run the following commands:


  2- Create symbolic links (Not needed for Ubuntu/Linux):
    $> ln -sf ~/.vim/vimrc ~/.vimrc
    $> ln -sf ~/.vim/gvimrc ~/.gvimrc

  3-  Install configured bundles:
    $> git clone https://github.com/gmarik/vundle.git ~/.vim/bundle/vundle
    -  Execute for the first time only
    $> vim -u ~/.vim/bundles.vim +BundleInstall +q
    Update modules, Launch vim, run :BundleInstall 

  4- ctags
     $> sudo apt-get install exuberant-ctags
     - Create c/cpp tags 
     $> cd ~/.vim/tags/
     $> tar xjf cpp_src.tar.bz2
     $> ./runCtags.sh
     $> rm -rf cpp_src

Install of sublimentary software

  1- vim-latexsuite on Ubuntu from command line as follows:
  $> sudo apt-get install vim-latexsuite
  $> sudo vim-addons -w install latex-suite



